      "writtenOn": "2025-12-04T02:59:05Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e And PCIe Endpoint side\u0027s PCIe VDM transport layer has no idea of this MCTP payload\u0027s real size.\n\nSure it does - it has the Pad Len field to calculate the actual size. See the packet formats in section 6.2.\n\n\u003e I feel this will be not the role of transport layer to decode MCTP packet itself.\n\nI agree, but it *is* the transport layer\u0027s role to preserve the correct framing of messages.",
